<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="20997" type="notes">
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="20997">Notes</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="20997">
Questionable status. Reported from Greece by 
<bibRefCitation author="Tselepides, Anastasios" journalOrPublisher="PhD thesis. University of Crete, Heraklion" pageId="0" pageNumber="20997" title="Οικολογική μελέτη τον βαθΰαλου οικοσυστήματος του Αιγαίου πελάγους" year="1992">Tselepides (1992)</bibRefCitation>
, but its presence in the Mediterranean is questioned by 
<bibRefCitation author="Ben-Eliahu, M. N." journalOrPublisher="Senckenbergiana Maritima" pageId="0" pageNumber="20997" pagination="1 - 51" title="Serpulid tube-worms (Annelida: Polychaeta) of the Central and Eastern Mediterranean with particular attention to the Levant Basin" volume="28" year="1996">Ben-Eliahu and Fiege (1996)</bibRefCitation>
, as 
<bibRefCitation author="Zibrowius, Helmut" journalOrPublisher="Bulletin of the British Museum (Natural History)" pageId="0" pageNumber="20997" pagination="427 - 439" title="Revision of some Serpulidae (AnnelidaPolychaeta) from abyssal depths in the Atlantic and Pacific, collected by the ' Challenger' and Prince of Monaco Expeditions" volume="24" year="1973">Zibrowius (1973a)</bibRefCitation>
had studied all Mediterranean specimens available to him and found that they belong in fact to other species.
</paragraph>
